question: Question: Regarding these objects, the speaker of the poem in which they appear says that "they were so delicious / so sweet / and so cold." For 10 points each: [10] Name these objects that were eaten by the narrator of the poem "This is Just to Say," even though his wife was "probably saving [them] for breakfast."
